.\" shell.1 - manual page for shell
.TH SHELL 1 "July 2026" "1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
shell \- show current shell name
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B shell [OPTION]
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -v, --verbose
Show detailed information (shell, version, PID, executable, history)
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B shell
prints the name of the current interactive shell (bash, zsh, fish, etc.).
With -v, it also shows version, process ID, executable path, and history availability.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B shell
bash
.TP
.B shell -v
Shell: bash
Version: 5.2.15(1)-release
PID: 12345
Executable: /usr/bin/bash
History: available
.SH AUTHOR
Written by Serg
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR echo (1), ps (1)
